    descEn: "The Onufri Museum is housed in the Church of the Dormition of St Mary inside the Kala — one of the finest Byzantine churches in Albania. The museum holds an extraordinary collection of icons and ecclesiastical artefacts, but the centrepiece is the work of Onufri himself. Onufri was the greatest Albanian icon painter of the 16th century, famous across the Orthodox world for the vivid, almost luminous red he achieved in his pigments — a formula that has never been fully replicated. His icons hang in churches from Serbia to Greece, but the collection here is the most concentrated anywhere.",
