    descEn: "Mangalem is the Muslim quarter of old Berat, cascading down the hillside below the castle in rows of white-plastered houses with their distinctive large windows facing south — the feature that gave Berat its nickname 'City of a Thousand Windows.' The Ottoman architecture here is exceptionally well-preserved, recognised by UNESCO as a rare surviving example of the domestic architecture of the period. Walking the stone-paved lanes in the evening, when the light catches the windows, is one of those quietly extraordinary travel experiences.",
