    descEn: "Standing south-east of Berat, Mount Tomor (2,416 metres) dominates the landscape for a hundred kilometres in every direction. In Albanian legend, Tomor and Shpirag — two mountains that flank the Osum valley — were brothers who fought a furious battle over a beautiful girl named Kala (the word for 'castle'). They threw mountains at each other so violently that pieces scattered across the valley floor. Neither won; both were turned to stone, condemned to stand opposite each other for eternity. Every August, thousands of Bektashi Muslims make a pilgrimage to the summit of Tomor for the Tekke of Abaz Ali — one of the most important religious gatherings in the country.",
